      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7fae89d083c6da1a",
      "text": "You are forced to choose a side [⇒ [[Die Gewalt der Zwei-Seiten-Form]]], even if you don't know exactly where you stand on the continuous spectrum. Because no one can hide behind the statement: \"I was born this way.\" The fact that there should then be another category, namely \"diverse\", is unhelpful or even counterproductive. After all, any kind of categorization leads to new discrimination – and the danger is even greater with three categories than with two."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "de739c26def4d50f",
      "text": "In its 2017 ruling, the German Constitutional Court even left it up to the legislator to abolish the registration of gender categories altogether. After all, if gender equality is guaranteed under constitutional law, the state no longer needs to know which gender someone feels they belong to. A reduction in bureaucracy would have been more than appropriate here. But our deeply rooted categorization thinking obviously lacked the courage to do so. When will we start thinking in terms of continuous distributions instead of [[Categories]]?"
